HEADWORD: Munificent
<hw>Mu*nif"i*cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>munificus</ets>; <ets>munus</ets> service, gift +
<ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to make. Cf. <er>Immunity</er>,
<er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>Very liberal in giving or bestowing; lavish;
<as>as, a <ex>munificent</ex> benefactor</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Mu*nif"i*cent*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Bounteous; bountiful; liberal; generous.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Munify</ent>⟦br⟧
